<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 93 / World Trade News: French radio system sold to UAE
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BUCHAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THOMSON-CSF, the French defence electronics company, has won a Dollars 100m
(Pounds 67m) order to supply the United Arab Emirates with its PR4G military
radio system.
The system, which has already been sold to the Netherlands, Spain and
Switzerland, will be used in various vehicles, including the Leclerc tank
ordered from Giat of France.
