   By CATHERINE MILTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SHARES IN Bluebird Toys hit a new high for the year yesterday after the
company said that pre-tax profits were likely to be 'substantially higher'
than current City forecasts of just over Pounds 5m.
The shares, which hit a low of 26p in December 1990, closed at 570p, up 90p
on the day.
In September, the company announced pre-tax profits of Pounds 1.99m (Pounds
234,000) for the six months to June. At that time Mr Torquil Norman,
chairman, said he expected continued growth in the second half as well as a
good result for 1993 as a whole.
