<HEADLINE>
FT  17 NOV 93 / Italy to lease spare RAF jets
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WHITE, Defence Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE MINISTRY of Defence is expected to earn Pounds 110m by leasing spare RAF
Tornado jets to the Italian air force.
Mr Fabio Fabbri, Italian defence minister, said in London yesterday that the
Tornado F3 air defence fighter had been chosen in preference to similar
licensing proposals involving two US aircraft, the Grumman F-14 and the
McDonnell Douglas F-15.
He added that Italy wanted to use the deal to launch closer defence
collaboration between the two countries.
The MoD confirmed that a leasing arrangement had been discussed but said no
agreement had been signed.
In addition to the payment to Britain, the plan also involves some L430bn
(Pounds 176m) worth of work for Italian industry including provision of
spares and support.
Italy wants the jets to replace its ageing F-104 Starfighters before
delivery of the new four-nation Eurofighter 2000.
</TEXT>
<XX>
