FT  17 NOV 93 / Syria accused over flare-up: Pro-Israeli militiamen captured
in Lebanon
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID HOROVITZ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   JERUSALEM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ISRAEL yesterday accused Syria of fomenting a worsening of hostilities in
southern Lebanon, during which 12 members of a pro-Israeli militia were
captured by Hizbollah gunmen.
Yesterday's violence was the worst since Israel and the Palestine Liberation
Organisation signed their peace accords in Washington two months ago.
Israeli ministers claimed Syria had ordered the Hizbollah attacks, out of
